JOHANNESBURG - Sunday will see a boxing tournament of eight bouts take place at Emperors Palace.The main fight on the card is without a doubt the South African Welterweight title bout between Shaun Ness and Thulani Mbenge.READ: 2016 SA boxing promoter Thysse, to host first tournament of the yearNess is the South African champion with the highly-rated Mbenge looking to take his belt.As part of the build-up to the fight, Mbenge and his trainer/manager Sean Smith came into the eNCA studio for a chat.Watch the full interview below: eNCA